<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-08T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-08T03:35:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9491/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-08T12:00:00+03:25">February
                                    8, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>34. Soon after receipt of Department’s number 13, January 19, I took up
                            the matter informally with Prime Minister who was noncommittal. The
                            Foreign Minister<note n="81" xml:id="d375fn81">All Soheily.</note>
                            promised me yesterday that he will have the question brought up at an
                            early Cabinet meeting.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>